<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - REMOVE AND
        INSTALL - FENDER EXTENSIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension Removal</title>
            <para>The fender extensions are part of the body splash protection system. The wheel well openings in the
                fender extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. These protect the lower
                front of the cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the step
                cleaner (
                <hotlnk document="s09006_9.xml" xrefid="f0900609">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s09006_18.xml" xrefid="f0900631">Figure 31</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the fender extension mounting bolts and nuts on the fender extension assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s09006_18.xml" xrefid="f0900631">Items 1, 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the three mounting bolts on the rear surface of the fender
                    extension.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the stud mounting nut (
                    <hotlnk document="s09006_18.xml" xrefid="f0900631">Item 2</hotlnk>) from the fender extension
                    mounting stud.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fender extension.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure to remove opposite side fender extension.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900632" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900632.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Fender Extension (Drivers Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING HOLES (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CAB STUD FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900633" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900633.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Fender Extension Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING BOLTS (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING STUD WITH NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension Install</title>
            <para>With hood in the tilted position, locate the fender extension mounting stud on the cab lower forward
                structure (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900632">Item 3, Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900634.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Fender Extension Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FENDER EXTENSION BOLT MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING STUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the fender extension mounting hole on the mounting stud (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900632">Item 4, Figure 32</hotlnk>), install mounting nut. Hand tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the mounting holes on the fender extension with the mounting holes on the lower
                    cab structure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install mounting bolts and lock washers and tighten to 46 - 51 Nm (34 - 38 lbf-ft).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the mounting nut on the fender extension mounting stud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque the mounting bolts to 41 - 51 Nm (30 - 38 lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Latch Lower Assembly Removal</title>
            <para>The hood latching mechanism consists of two parts. The lower lock portion of the latching mechanism is
                located on the fender extension assembly (Item 1, Figure 34).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900635" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900635.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Lower Hood Latch</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER HOOD HATCH CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BOLT MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Hood latch clip removal:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release hood latch both sides and tilt hood forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate mounting bolts, hex nuts and washers, loosen and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hatch clip assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure on opposite side for lower latch clip assembly removal.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Lower Hood Latch Install</title>
            <figure id="f0900636" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Lower Hood Latch</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER HOOD LATCHING ATTACHMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLTS AND FLAT WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FENDER EXTENSION LATCH MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEX HEAD NUTS AND LOCK WASHERS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the latch clip mounting holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the latch clip on the fender extension aligning the mounting holes with the
                    holes in the fender extension.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert mounting bolts and flat washers through the latch clip assembly and fender
                    assembly mounting holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900634">Item 2, Figure 34</hotlnk>) .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the hex nuts and lock washers on the mounting bolts and tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque nuts to 28 - 37 Nm (21 - 27 lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
